  "2026-04-07T08:09:27.158Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence commands: pm context --limit 10; pm list-open --limit 50; pm list-in-progress --limit 50; pm search no-pager non-interactive help paging --limit 10. Net-new because no active item directly covers non-TTY help paging safeguards and first-class --no-pager support."
  "2026-04-07T08:14:45.826Z",codex-agent,"Implementation in progress: wiring global --no-pager option, bootstrap parser handling, non-TTY help pager auto-disable policy, and parity updates for contracts/completion/Pi/tests/docs."
  "2026-04-07T08:17:35.193Z",codex-agent,"Completed implementation: added global --no-pager option, bootstrap parsing, and non-TTY help auto pager-disable policy via PAGER/MANPAGER/GIT_PAGER=cat. Propagated to contracts/completion/Pi/help text with focused regression suite passing (132 tests): node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/completion-command.spec.ts tests/unit/pi-agent-extension.spec.ts tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts."
  "2026-04-07T09:06:42.406Z",codex-agent,"Post-implementation verification caught a compatibility regression from the new global --no-pager switch: extension command handler contexts were receiving a default pager=true option in context.options. Fixed by excluding global pager state from command-scoped extension options in src/cli/main.ts (extractCommandScopedOptions) so dynamic command option payloads remain command-specific and backward-compatible. Re-ran focused integration suite (cli/help/release-readiness) and then full sandboxed test + coverage runs successfully."
